questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a developer has implemented a custom cache using Spring and `List` structures. The snippet below is intended to ensure that every update to the list is isolated in its own database transaction to prevent data loss. However, metrics show that the `REQUIRES_NEW` transaction is never actually created, and the audit logs are missing entries when errors occur. 

java
@Service
public class DataAggregator {
    private final List<String> buffer = Collections.synchronizedList(new ArrayList<>());

    @Transactional
    public void processData(String item) {
        // Business logic
        saveToBuffer(item);
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void saveToBuffer(String item) {
        buffer.add(item);
        // Potential DB audit logging here
    }
}
